# Skills listed here (one name per line) are silently skipped by
# claude-capture. Use this for upstream-maintained or externally-managed
# skills that shouldn't live in git history.
#
# Format: one skill name per line (match the directory name under
# ~/.claude/skills/). Comments start with '#'. Blank lines are ignored.
#
# Note: Nix-managed skills (home.file with recursive=true, fetched from
# pinned upstream) are already auto-skipped because every leaf is a store
# symlink -- no entry needed here. This file is for the gap case:
# skills that are installed outside Nix but also outside your repo
# (e.g., experimental skills you're iterating on locally).
